France's Kristina Mladenovic and Croatia's Ivan Dodig won the Australian Open mixed doubes title. AFP/Brandon Malone MELBOURNE - France's Kristina Mladenovic and Croatia's Ivan Dodig were crowned Australian Open mixed doubles champions on Friday with a 6-3, 6-4 victory over Australian pair Jaimee Fourlis and Jason Kubler. It was a second Melbourne Park mixed doubles title for Mladenovic, who won in 2014 with Daniel Nestor. She also owns two women's doubles titles in Australia from 2018 and 2020. Veteran Dodig has three other Grand Slam mixed titles -- two at the French Open and one at Wimbledon, along with two men's doubles successes, including at last year's Australian Open with Filip Polasek. 